1
00:02:08,310 --> 00:02:13,300
They're developing quickly!
 They're absolutely superhuman!

2
00:02:13,940 --> 00:02:16,370
– Father!
– Father dearest!

3
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:23,030
I'm so proud of all of you!

4
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:32,250
My beloved children!

5
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:59,940
Where do they take the fancy food 
we've been making?

6
00:02:59,940 --> 00:03:02,950
I'm not sure. There aren't any guests in the castle.

7
00:03:02,950 --> 00:03:08,830
Don't be nosy! His Majesty 
ordered us to cook, so we're going to cook.

8
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:45,360
Sanji!

9
00:03:46,410 --> 00:03:50,460
Royalty mustn't serve anyone!
How many times do I have to tell you this?!

10
00:03:50,460 --> 00:03:52,620
Your mother is dead!

11
00:03:52,620 --> 00:03:55,390
Stop chasing her shadow!

12
00:04:03,050 --> 00:04:04,720
Ouch!

13
00:04:05,630 --> 00:04:07,050
Oh, boy!

14
00:04:07,050 --> 00:04:10,930
– Ow, ow, ow!
– Are you all right, Your Highness?!

15
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:15,760
His Majesty ordered us not to allow you into the kitchen.

16
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,270
Please!

17
00:04:17,270 --> 00:04:19,780
Let me... stay!

18
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:34,000
It's done!

19
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:47,660
– Where are you going all on your own?
– To see my mother.

20
00:04:47,660 --> 00:04:51,300
The medical ward is at the far end, 
and the weather is...

21
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,910
– I can do it.
– But...

22
00:04:52,910 --> 00:04:54,360
Don't follow me!

23
00:04:57,730 --> 00:04:59,900
And don't tell my father.

24
00:05:11,580 --> 00:05:13,680
Get back inside!

25
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:33,470
What?! This isn't your food!

26
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:46,490
S-Stop!

27
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:03,170
Y-Your Highness!

28
00:06:03,170 --> 00:06:05,440
Did you come here all on your own?!

29
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:13,760
I appreciate the sentiment.

30
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:18,690
But we can't let Her Majesty's stomach hurt.

31
00:06:21,150 --> 00:06:25,460
Still, maybe it tastes better than it...

32
00:06:29,740 --> 00:06:31,780
What?!

33
00:06:44,460 --> 00:06:45,800
Sanji!

34
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:49,130
Did you come to visit me in this storm?

35
00:06:49,130 --> 00:06:52,230
If your father finds out, he'll be furious.

36
00:06:52,230 --> 00:06:54,430
– Uh-huh.
– Your Majesty.

37
00:06:55,510 --> 00:06:57,560
This is from Prince Sanji.

38
00:07:01,110 --> 00:07:03,860
Did you make this for me?

39
00:07:03,860 --> 00:07:05,980
I... I did.

40
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:10,700
Époni!

41
00:07:10,700 --> 00:07:12,440
Y-Yes, Your Majesty!

42
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:17,420
Don't be presumptuous!
Hand over what Sanji cooked for me!

43
00:07:17,420 --> 00:07:20,180
Well, okay.

44
00:07:20,180 --> 00:07:25,410
But it was damaged on his way here,
so I threw it in the trash.

45
00:07:25,410 --> 00:07:26,670
– Bring it to me!
– Yes, ma'am!

46
00:07:30,970 --> 00:07:32,780
Wow, nice!

47
00:07:32,780 --> 00:07:36,720
Scrambled eggs, fish, and bananas?

48
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:39,230
I'm sorry, Mother!

49
00:07:39,230 --> 00:07:41,260
I messed it up!

50
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:43,900
I tripped and dropped it on my way here.

51
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:46,650
It's been crushed and got wet in the rain.

52
00:07:46,650 --> 00:07:48,300
Let's try it.

53
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:55,950
Yummy!

54
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,760
What?!

55
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:03,120
– Really?!
– Yes!

56
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:05,420
Mother!

57
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:08,920
Sanji, will you cook for me again?

58
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:11,150
Uh-huh!

59
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:33,700
Mother!

60
00:08:34,630 --> 00:08:38,120
Sanji, will you cook for me again?

61
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,760
You want cookbooks and utensils?

62
00:09:18,060 --> 00:09:20,330
"All... Blue"?

63
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:24,160
"Where fish from all four seas live,"

64
00:09:25,550 --> 00:09:27,700
"a legendary sea"!

65
00:09:32,340 --> 00:09:34,720
See! I told you Sanji was down here.

66
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:38,550
You're right! That's totally him!

67
00:09:39,070 --> 00:09:43,680
So he's still alive after all! 
Why did Father lie to us?

68
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:45,810
Probably because he wishes he were dead.

69
00:09:47,770 --> 00:09:53,800
In that case, if he really dies, 
will Father be happy?

70
00:10:17,650 --> 00:10:18,970
Stop it!

71
00:10:21,350 --> 00:10:26,880
You're a failure who deserves to die, Sanji!

72
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:41,910
Ow...

73
00:10:41,910 --> 00:10:46,410
Don't assume that I'm on your side.
I don't want to get dragged into this!

74
00:10:47,050 --> 00:10:50,860
Those three are Father's ideal soldiers.

75
00:10:50,860 --> 00:10:54,960
They lack emotions like pity, sympathy, and even sadness.

76
00:10:57,470 --> 00:11:02,640
My body was successfully augmented,
but that's one area where I'm different from them.

77
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:04,860
See you later.

78
00:11:04,860 --> 00:11:07,400
Th-Thank you, Reiju.

79
00:11:08,430 --> 00:11:12,520
Oh, right. 
We climb the Red Line soon.

80
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:16,440
We're going to wage war in the East Blue.

81
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:18,960
War?

82
00:11:20,860 --> 00:11:24,280
Set course for the East Blue!

83
00:11:34,130 --> 00:11:37,650
The estimate arrival time is three weeks.

84
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:42,570
Reiju, I...

85
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:52,130
I...

86
00:12:52,130 --> 00:12:54,080
want to be a cook!

87
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:58,500
Fire!

88
00:13:00,170 --> 00:13:04,300
– It's Germa 66.
– What?! They're real?!

89
00:13:09,180 --> 00:13:11,220
What's going on?!

90
00:13:11,220 --> 00:13:15,480
Generalissimo Judge, 
our targets in Cozia have noticed us!

91
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:18,230
Crush them!

92
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:24,150
So, like I said, 
don't tell me something like that!

93
00:13:28,020 --> 00:13:31,620
If I can... while in the East Blue...

94
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:38,460
If I can escape,

95
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:43,150
I'll never have to see...

96
00:13:43,980 --> 00:13:46,060
Father's face...

97
00:13:46,690 --> 00:13:49,760
ever again, right?

98
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:58,980
Step back!

99
00:14:03,690 --> 00:14:05,860
This is your only chance!

100
00:14:05,860 --> 00:14:07,700
Don't screw up!

101
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:17,570
Go ashore!

102
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,640
It's just begun!

103
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:35,150
The key to your iron mask is
in our father's room! Go get it!

104
00:14:35,150 --> 00:14:36,420
What?!

105
00:14:36,420 --> 00:14:38,480
I'm gonna go see what's going on outside!

106
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:40,060
Okay?!

107
00:14:40,060 --> 00:14:41,110
Y-Yeah!

108
00:14:41,110 --> 00:14:45,110
When you get into his room,
look for a skull symbol on the wall!

109
00:14:45,110 --> 00:14:47,850
You'll find a safe there!

110
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:04,960
I got it!

111
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:07,920
What are you doing over there?

112
00:15:11,990 --> 00:15:16,470
Sanji-kun, why are you here?!

113
00:15:21,260 --> 00:15:22,350
Father...

114
00:15:27,630 --> 00:15:32,770
I'm leaving this country!
Don't try to stop me!

115
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:37,950
It seems your imprisonment has harshened your words.

116
00:15:37,950 --> 00:15:44,920
An ordinary boy such as yourself has 
no chance of surviving in this or any other sea.

117
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:48,210
You will die!

118
00:15:54,670 --> 00:15:58,130
So what?! You can't stop me!

119
00:15:58,130 --> 00:15:59,770
That's a relief!

120
00:16:01,190 --> 00:16:04,460
I guess I'm human after all.

121
00:16:04,460 --> 00:16:10,820
Even though you're useless, 
I couldn't bring myself to kill my own son.

122
00:16:11,690 --> 00:16:14,360
But you want to leave on your own?

123
00:16:17,910 --> 00:16:24,040
I will not stop you.
Take the key to that iron mask and leave.

124
00:16:27,170 --> 00:16:34,760
But I have one more thing 
to ask as your father, Sanji.

125
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:41,890
Don't ever admit that I'm your father...

126
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:47,060
to even a single person!

127
00:16:52,710 --> 00:16:56,070
I do not want anyone to learn of my shame.

128
00:16:56,920 --> 00:16:58,840
Do you understand?

129
00:17:47,790 --> 00:17:50,200
What should we do about the cruise ship at the port?!

130
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:54,590
They aren't our target!
There's just in the wrong place! Leave them alone!

131
00:17:57,760 --> 00:17:59,390
Get on that ship!

132
00:17:59,970 --> 00:18:04,140
Sanji! You're a boy! Stop crying already!

133
00:18:05,740 --> 00:18:09,400
Listen! Don't ever come back here!

134
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:10,310
Uh-huh!

135
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:15,720
The sea's a huge place! You'll...

136
00:18:17,530 --> 00:18:22,990
You'll definitely find people who will accept you!

137
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:27,830
Run!

138
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:33,000
Don't look back!

139
00:18:38,510 --> 00:18:42,220
Run! Sanji!

140
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:36,270
Yummy! It's nice and crunchy!

141
00:19:36,270 --> 00:19:37,360
Yes!

142
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:41,240
He ate Minister Cracker's biscuit soldiers!

143
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,780
What?!

144
00:19:42,780 --> 00:19:45,410
How dare you eat them!

145
00:19:45,410 --> 00:19:48,040
Biscuits are food!

146
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:52,460
That's right, Luffy! 
Once you eat them, they can't come back!

147
00:19:52,460 --> 00:19:54,540
Eat as many of them as you can!

148
00:19:54,540 --> 00:19:58,260
What a crafty woman!

149
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:27,280
Oh, no. Is he conscious?

150
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:34,750
Get out of my way.

151
00:20:34,750 --> 00:20:38,750
Oh, Lady Reiju, we're about to treat his...

152
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:40,800
I said get out of my way!

153
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,300
I'm sorry!

154
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:50,340
Good grief.

155
00:20:50,340 --> 00:20:54,190
Are you going to meet your fiancée with that face?

156
00:20:55,580 --> 00:21:01,180
This could've all been avoided if you had just forgotten about that restaurant owner.

157
00:21:02,150 --> 00:21:04,030
Why did you come back?

158
00:21:05,220 --> 00:21:10,040
I thought that you wanted to forget about this place?

159
00:21:10,040 --> 00:21:11,450
Sanji.

160
00:21:35,020 --> 00:21:38,020
I-I'm stuffed now.

161
00:21:38,020 --> 00:21:40,160
Screw you!

162
00:21:42,030 --> 00:21:46,160
I'm sick of fighting you already!

163
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:51,950
You fight, run away, then come back and eat!

164
00:21:54,370 --> 00:21:56,770
Is he really human?!

165
00:21:56,770 --> 00:22:00,670
Minister Cracker is amazing,
 but so is Straw Hat's appetite!

166
00:22:01,210 --> 00:22:03,230
Minister Cracker...

167
00:22:03,230 --> 00:22:07,090
Hey, are his biscuits really infinite?

168
00:22:07,090 --> 00:22:09,050
Yes, that's right.

169
00:22:09,050 --> 00:22:12,470
But his stamina can't be!

170
00:22:12,470 --> 00:22:14,580
I'll outlast you!

171
00:22:14,580 --> 00:22:19,440
Eat until you burst!
 Then your comrades will give up!

172
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:21,610
I'll eat every last one!

173
00:22:21,610 --> 00:22:24,780
I'll eat and eat and take Sanji back!

174
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:30,230
I'll bring out more biscuit soldiers for you, then.

175
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:38,370
Eat them and pop, Straw Hat!

176
00:22:40,210 --> 00:22:42,840
And...

177
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:48,160
I'll tell Mama that you aided them, Kingbaum!

178
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:51,390
What?! But you already chopped off the top of my head!

179
00:22:51,390 --> 00:22:54,470
That's not fair, Minister Cracker!

180
00:22:54,470 --> 00:23:00,730
She's using the power 
of Mama's vivre card against us!

181
00:23:00,730 --> 00:23:03,980
So, in a way, we are obeying Mama!

182
00:23:04,020 --> 00:23:08,860
Save your excuses for Mama! 
The fact is, you interfered with my mission!

183
00:23:09,910 --> 00:23:16,370
If it weren't for her rain,
 my hard biscuit soldiers

184
00:23:16,370 --> 00:23:20,420
wouldn't have softened up 
into tasty, chewable snacks!

185
00:23:20,420 --> 00:23:24,450
Shut up! This is a fight between pirates!

186
00:23:24,450 --> 00:23:28,920
We figured out your weakness, but that doesn't mean you should take it out on my soldiers!

187
00:23:29,010 --> 00:23:30,430
Your?!

188
00:23:30,430 --> 00:23:31,740
Are we...

189
00:23:31,740 --> 00:23:34,100
...her soldiers now?!

190
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:36,600
What was that?

191
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:38,600
We're sorry!

192
00:23:39,770 --> 00:23:43,010
Let's put an end to this, biscuit soldiers!

193
00:23:45,510 --> 00:23:47,570
This should end it!

194
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:53,780
I guess I gotta eat them.
They'll keep coming if I break them.

195
00:23:53,780 --> 00:23:55,270
But...

196
00:23:55,270 --> 00:23:57,700
I'm getting pretty full now.

197
00:23:57,700 --> 00:24:01,070
Make sure to protect me, homies!

198
00:24:01,070 --> 00:24:02,170
G-Got it!

199
00:24:02,170 --> 00:24:06,400
Hey, Nami, can I try something other than eating them?

200
00:24:07,300 --> 00:24:10,200
I'll fight them for a while, and then continue.

201
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,920
Weather Egg!

202
00:24:12,590 --> 00:24:16,010
I don't care if you're related to an emperor...

203
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:20,770
Luffy's going to be the pirate king!

204
00:24:20,770 --> 00:24:24,020
So there's no limit to his appetite!

205
00:24:24,100 --> 00:24:28,230
What?! Nami, I've been eating all night!

206
00:24:28,230 --> 00:24:31,760
Is his stomach bottomless?

207
00:24:31,760 --> 00:24:32,740
No...

208
00:24:32,740 --> 00:24:34,740
Rain Spark!

209
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:43,750
The soldiers are going to soften up again! Stop!

210
00:24:44,930 --> 00:24:46,540
No... I can't...

211
00:25:01,220 --> 00:25:03,520
Wait for me, Sanji!

212
00:25:03,520 --> 00:25:05,910
Dammit!

213
00:25:15,220 --> 00:25:17,370
Look at that gluttony!

214
00:25:26,620 --> 00:25:29,340
Generalissimo Judge, it is time.

215
00:25:29,340 --> 00:25:32,080
The preparations are complete.

216
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:35,340
Good, inform my children.

217
00:25:35,340 --> 00:25:38,890
We're leaving for Whole Cake Chateau!

218
00:25:40,560 --> 00:25:43,090
Ready? This might sting a little.

219
00:25:43,090 --> 00:25:44,480
Just hurry up and do it.

220
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:47,370
It feels a little weird...

221
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:53,690
Don't touch it.

222
00:25:55,740 --> 00:25:56,860
How does it feel?

223
00:26:03,950 --> 00:26:05,830
The swelling has gone down.

224
00:26:05,830 --> 00:26:06,910
Ouch!

225
00:26:06,910 --> 00:26:09,980
That pack only works for swelling.

226
00:26:09,980 --> 00:26:15,420
It's suppressing the body's normal response,
so it's actually preventing it from healing.

227
00:26:15,420 --> 00:26:18,950
But it's better than your fiancée seeing your swollen face.

228
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:25,350
The members of the Charlotte family 
don't take their spouses' family name.

229
00:26:25,510 --> 00:26:28,980
So if they accept you as a part of their family,
 you can live a happy life.

230
00:26:29,670 --> 00:26:31,220
Damn you...

231
00:26:31,220 --> 00:26:36,190
You came back on your own.
I don't owe you anything.

232
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:38,320
You won't get another chance.

233
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:47,370
By the way, where did you 
pick up that sense of chivalry?

234
00:26:52,750 --> 00:26:57,260
Women! Women! Women! Women!

235
00:26:57,260 --> 00:26:58,840
Women!

236
00:27:00,430 --> 00:27:04,370
Shut up! We don't need a female chef!

237
00:27:06,020 --> 00:27:08,730
Cut it out!

238
00:27:11,020 --> 00:27:15,020
I'm the type of man that 
reinforces my lessons through kicks.

239
00:27:15,020 --> 00:27:17,990
I can't do that to a woman!

240
00:27:17,990 --> 00:27:22,030
Why not?! If she doesn't listen, then just kick her, too!

241
00:27:22,030 --> 00:27:24,430
You idiot!

242
00:27:27,830 --> 00:27:30,120
Ouch!

243
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:33,130
A man can't kick a woman!

244
00:27:33,130 --> 00:27:37,050
That's been the rule
since the age of the dinosaurs!

245
00:27:38,420 --> 00:27:40,500
Listen, little eggplant!

246
00:27:40,500 --> 00:27:43,550
You can make all kinds
of mistakes as a human being!

247
00:27:43,550 --> 00:27:47,180
But if you ever fail at being a proper man,

248
00:27:47,180 --> 00:27:51,560
I'll cut off your balls,
and slit my own throat!

249
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:54,860
What?! Why would you do that to yourself?!

250
00:27:58,360 --> 00:28:01,150
That's how a parent owns up to their mistake!

251
00:28:03,240 --> 00:28:07,370
You fool... Don't become
the type of person I despise.

252
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:13,540
Now, get back to work.

253
00:28:17,530 --> 00:28:20,280
That's been the rule 
since the age of the dinosaurs.

254
00:28:32,270 --> 00:28:34,730
Sanji, Your Highness, it's time to leave.

255
00:28:34,730 --> 00:28:39,070
You all are going to the engagement ceremony at Whole Cake Chateau.

256
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:46,860
Put this shirt on.

257
00:28:46,860 --> 00:28:50,240
You're a member of the Vinsmoke royal family.

258
00:28:50,290 --> 00:28:53,650
You need to look the part.

259
00:28:53,650 --> 00:28:55,380
What a joke...

260
00:29:07,010 --> 00:29:10,640
Meanwhile, in Brûlée's Mirro-world...

261
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:13,770
I found you!

262
00:29:15,940 --> 00:29:19,270
She's back!

263
00:29:21,260 --> 00:29:23,400
You can't escape!

264
00:29:32,790 --> 00:29:35,800
I can't run anymore, Chobro!

265
00:29:37,460 --> 00:29:40,670
Stop running around all of my mirrors!

266
00:29:48,150 --> 00:29:50,690
Have a great wedding ceremony!

267
00:29:54,140 --> 00:29:56,650
Congratulations!

268
00:29:56,650 --> 00:29:58,600
Prince Sanji!

269
00:30:02,570 --> 00:30:06,490
Today is a new beginning 
for the Vinsmoke family.

270
00:30:15,120 --> 00:30:17,960
Prince Sanji!

271
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:21,590
Wave to the citizens, Sanji.

272
00:30:39,310 --> 00:30:41,730
Let's go, guys!

273
00:31:01,010 --> 00:31:03,560
I've had enough, you guys!

274
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:06,550
I seriously can't eat anymore!

275
00:31:08,530 --> 00:31:09,930
At your limit, huh?

276
00:31:09,930 --> 00:31:15,430
I'll never throw up something that I've eaten!

277
00:31:17,640 --> 00:31:23,150
Then, I'll make it easy for you 
by stabbing your belly!

278
00:31:23,150 --> 00:31:24,660
Look out, Luffy!

279
00:31:25,610 --> 00:31:28,280
That's it! I'm ending this now!

280
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:30,680
Muscle Balloon!

281
00:31:53,090 --> 00:31:54,300
What the...?!

282
00:32:15,280 --> 00:32:17,580
Gear Fourth!

283
00:32:23,170 --> 00:32:28,000
Tankman: Stuffed Version!

284
00:32:30,380 --> 00:32:32,170
What?! He's huge!

285
00:32:39,290 --> 00:32:43,480
You look quite different
from your first transformation.

286
00:32:43,480 --> 00:32:47,020
Can you fight with that big fat body?!

287
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:55,610
Minister Cracker's blade can't cut him!

288
00:32:55,610 --> 00:32:57,160
How hard is he?!

289
00:32:58,990 --> 00:33:02,750
You snot-nosed brat!

290
00:33:05,430 --> 00:33:08,550
Don't push your luck!

291
00:33:09,360 --> 00:33:12,470
Straw Hat!

292
00:33:12,470 --> 00:33:16,390
If I can't cut you, I'll just stab you!

293
00:33:16,390 --> 00:33:17,690
Honey...

294
00:33:19,050 --> 00:33:20,600
Pretzel!

295
00:33:24,760 --> 00:33:26,020
Not yet!

296
00:33:26,020 --> 00:33:28,980
With this thrust, you'll burst!

297
00:33:31,440 --> 00:33:34,650
Crush Pretzel!

298
00:33:43,540 --> 00:33:45,290
Luffy!

299
00:33:53,260 --> 00:33:56,760
What is this? Is it hard or soft?

300
00:33:59,050 --> 00:34:02,260
Wha...? What the hell is this?!

301
00:34:04,430 --> 00:34:05,980
Biscuit soldiers!

302
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:09,900
Rain!

303
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:09,900
Nami!

304
00:34:09,900 --> 00:34:14,860
Don't make it rain on the biscuits anymore!
They can stay hard!

305
00:34:14,860 --> 00:34:16,450
Okay!

306
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:30,500
I can't get out! What's he gonna do?!

307
00:34:30,540 --> 00:34:33,780
I'll show you the power of a full stomach!

308
00:34:34,760 --> 00:34:37,420
Gum-Gum...

309
00:34:59,990 --> 00:35:02,760
Cannonball!

310
00:34:52,190 --> 00:34:55,460
Fly away...

311
00:34:55,460 --> 00:34:58,400
to the end of the New World!

